                     <title type="Complete">Mäṣḥafä täklil “The Book of the Marriage Ritual”</title>
                     <rubric>Nomina sacra; name of the reigning monarch; incipits of the texts; directives to the ministers; elements of the punctuation signs; elements of Ethiopic numerals.&#xD;
The text on fol. 3r is written alternately in red and black lines.</rubric>
                     <incipit defective="false">Fol. 3ra, l.1:በስመ፡ አብ፡ ወወልድ፡ ወመንፈስ፡ ቅዱስ፡ ፩አምላክ፡ ንቀድም፡ በረድኤተ፡ እግዚአብሔር፡ ጸሒፈ፡ መጽሐፈ፡ ተክሊል፡ ዘውእቱ፡ ሕገ፡ ሰብሳብ፡ ዝንቱ፡ ውእቱ፡ ቀዳማዊ፡ ጸሎት፡ ዘይትነበብ፡ ላዕለ፡ አልባሰ፡ መርዓዊ፡ ወመርዓት፨<foreign xml:lang="en">[Fol. 3ra, l.1]: In the name of the Father, the Son and the Holy Spirit, One God. Let us commence, with God’s help, to write the Book of the Crowning which is the ritual of marriage. This is the first prayer which is read over the garments of the bridegroom and bride.</foreign>
                     </incipit>
                     <explicit defective="false">Fol. 32ra, l.13: ይበል፡ ካህን፡ ዘቀደሰ። ድኅረ፡ ጸሎተ፡ መባእ፡ ክርስቶስ፡ አምላክነ፡ ዘሖርከ። ውስተ፡ ከብካብ፡ እስከ፡ ተፍጻሜቱ።።።<foreign xml:lang="en">[Fol. 32ra, l.13]: Let the celebrant priest recite after the prayer of the offering: “Christ our God who went to the wedding…” up to the end.</foreign>
                     </explicit>
